Even so, they should rather provide the plate with ventilation holes (if there are none in it) and mattresses with spring skeleton and 15 cm minimum height with so-called. Use pocket spring core and fine pads.
Polyurethane mattresses do not belong on such a base.
Latex or sandwich mattresses (if necessary also combinations of latex and coconut) are suitable for non-adjustable slatted frames with 14 to 18 spring strips (if necessary also combinations of latex and coconut), always rusts with a larger number of slats, i.e. 28 and more spring strips, with lordosis support in the lumbar region and the possibility of regulating the slat hardness.
On adjustable slat grates, there are no mattresses with feather skeleton, as they do not respond to the ergonomic adjustment.
In addition to adjusting the stiffness of the spring strips, special flexible shoulder modules are also offered.
This is a special attachment of the spring strips, which makes it possible to press in the spring strips or even to angle them in such a way that they enable the shoulder of the sleeper to sink in a point.
Especially for men with broad shoulders an important thing.
There are even mattress manufacturers who have started to use soft zones for the shoulder area in "men's mattresses".
Also thought of the ladies - they are granted these soft zones in the hip area.
For the most demanding customers, point-elastic wing spring systems (Lattoflex) or grates with point-elastic contact pads with so-called Multitorsion suspension determined.
The pressure is spread over several points, which reduces the voltage.
But - if you use a bad (too large and full) pillow to the right mattress and right rust, most of the benefits are lost again.
Again, a rule of thumb: the pillow should support the head, its tips should only reach up to the shoulders so that the shoulder muscles can relax.
