The U.S. is changing the rules for obtaining a visa
People must present themselves to the visa application services department before they are interviewed at the consulate; this will reduce waiting times.
From the 10. In January 2011, the procedures for applying for a visa in the United States Embassy and in the consulates are changing.
In the new procedure, most applicants must present themselves to the visa application services agencies (ASC, the initial letters) before their conversation in the consulate.
The personnel of the ASC shall record the biometric data of the applicant, which will be reviewed by the consulate before the interview.
The new method has certain advantages for the aspirants, including:
The total cost of processing the visa decreases, because it is no longer necessary to pay separately the appointment, the processing of the visa application and the transport service with which the document is handed out.
The applicant makes only a single payment covering the three services.
The current price remains unchanged: the equivalent of 140 dollars for a tourist visa, 150 dollars for visas with application (including visas for temporary workers) and 390 dollars for hands and investors.
Those who only want to renew their visa do not have to have a conversation in the consulate, they only have to introduce themselves to the nearest ASC, where they will present their documents and their fingerprints will be taken.
Since the biometric data is collected in the ASC, the applicants who need a second appointment for the conversation in the consulate remain there less time than before.
Those applying for the visa in the consulates of Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo will no longer have to pay the service surcharge of 26 dollars.
Additional information about the new visa application procedure can be found in the following website: http://mexico.usembassy.gov/boletines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
