Formerly, in Orwell's time, you could bundle all power like a Big Brother that controlled every gesture of his subjects.
Orwell's prophecy could have turned out to be perfectly right since then, where you can control every movement thanks to the phone, every transaction made, the hotel visited, the chosen highway, and so on; the citizen would become the total victim of the eye of power.
